<item>
            <title>[LU-14949] gap in rename atomicity: possible to get ENOENT when renaming over an existing file</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14949</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When doing a rename/mv of a file over the top of an existing file, there is a race with an open of that existing while where that open can get ENOENT.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This race is due to a combination of OPEN_BY_FID and our dentry caching behavior and can be resolved by a change to the handling of opens.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
